<hr>  <p>When I use Eclipse's java-conventions built-in java formatter, the formatter collapses multiple spaces into one space.</p>  <p>For example the following comment is</p>  <pre><code>//              5 //             / \ //            4   8 //           /   / \ //          11  13  4 //         /  \      \ //        7    2      1 </code></pre>  <p>is modified into after pressing ctrl + shift + f(windows)</p>  <pre><code>// 5 // / \ // 4 8 // / / \ // 11 13 4 // / \ \ // 7 2 1 </code></pre>  <p>How to configure Eclipse to not collapse the extra space.</p>